{
  "stem": "1169.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The only one who was still in Hungary were us, because we were in this large city, and the-- the mood in the large cities was more civilized, and always the large cities were the last ones to be deported.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But everyone else was already gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It was too late.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he also assembled, Kastner, 300 boys-- Jewish boys and girls, teenagers between the age of about 16 to 19, 20.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Not Hungarians-- Lithuanians who smuggled themselves into Hungary, who saw their parents being killed in front of their own eyes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And Lithuania, of course, is known for scholarship.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "These boys were Talmudic geniuses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the girls are also very well-learned.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The Lithuanian community, more than any other community, emphasized education-- very educated.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And Kastner put them on this group because they would be shot if found they were illegal in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "These boys and girls did not believe after this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "They were like atheists.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And the other people did not want to be too friendly with them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "My family became very friendly with them, and that's where our families career, which is, to this day, of working with Jews that are unaffiliated, or very removed, started.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we realized that when you see a Jew who's not observant, and you give them a hug and a kiss, he will respond.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And the train was assembled, and that's when we started to leave Budapest.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We also were in cattle cars, but the doors are open.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "It was a slow-moving train, and it was not packed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "We had about 30 people to a car, and the-- many people sat at the door with their feet dangling, as we took this trip.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And we came to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And then we stopped in an Austrian town called Linz.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
